# Form Action Button Rule

**Use `FormActionButton.astro` for all form buttons.** This ensures consistent styling across submit, cancel, next, prev, and skip actions.

## DO

```astro
import FormActionButton from "../components/form/FormActionButton.astro";

<!-- Submit -->
<FormActionButton action="submit" />
<FormActionButton action="submit" label="Save" />
<FormActionButton action="submit" label="Post Comment" icon="send" type="button" />

<!-- Cancel -->
<FormActionButton action="cancel" />
<FormActionButton action="cancel" id="cancel-btn" />

<!-- New (add/create) -->
<FormActionButton action="new" label="New Comment" />
<FormActionButton action="new" label="Add Punchlist Item" />
```

## DON'T

```astro
<!-- Do NOT use raw buttons for form actions -->
<button type="submit">Submit</button>
<button type="button">Cancel</button>

<!-- Do NOT use Button.astro for form submit/cancel -->
<Button type="submit" variant="primary">Submit</Button>
```

## Dynamic/JS-built forms

When building form HTML in JavaScript (e.g. table rows, injected templates), use `getFormActionButtonHTML()` from `src/lib/form-action-button-html.ts`:

```ts
import { getFormActionButtonHTML } from "./form-action-button-html";

const submitHtml = getFormActionButtonHTML("submit", { label: "Save", size: "sm" });
const cancelHtml = getFormActionButtonHTML("cancel", { size: "sm", className: "my-cancel", dataIdPlaceholder: "__ID__" });
// Replace __ID__ at runtime: cancelHtml.replace(/__ID__/g, String(id))
```

## Overlays and fixed positioning

**When a button is fixed on screen or over an image/hero**, use `variant="outline"` so the background shows through. Solid primary buttons block the view; outline keeps them legible while letting the background remain visible.

```astro
<!-- Fixed FAB, hero CTA, image overlay, etc. -->
<FormActionButton action="new" label="New" variant="outline" />
```

## Config

Defaults live in `GLOBAL_BUTTON_DEFAULTS` (src/lib/multi-step-form-config.ts). Change there to update all form buttons across the app.
